results.title: Set of arrows, vintage arrows, Kievan Rus, arrows, artefact,  rarity, collage, arrowheads
results.description:
A set of ancient arrows for the bow.
External dimensions - mm 213X164. Internal dimensions - mm 138X88. Weight - 320 grams.
It has a stand to place on a horizontal surface.
To keep the original product, they are fixed to the linen using a thread. In the future, you can fix with a water soluble adhesive. The use of other types of glue is not desirable. This may damage the product.

№ 1. Scythian battle tip.
The Scythians - the ancient warlike people, who in the VII century BC - in the III century BC lived in the northern Black Sea region (Currently, it is a region of Moldova, Ukraine and Russia). Therefore, we can assume that the artifact more than 2000 years. It has trihedral shape and is characterized by high technology, performance (for its time). They are made by casting and has a trihedral shape. Similar artifacts from later periods were not so technical. A characteristic feature of the Scythian tip is that when the arrow on the body can be removed only the shaft and the tip remains in the body. Length - 40mm.

Number 2 and 3. Martial lugs time of Kievan Rus XI-XIII century AD. Found near the city of Kiev, Ukraine. The length of the number 2 - 70 mm., Length number 3 - 62 mm.

Twin tip number 4 the time of Kievan Rus XI-XIII century AD. There are two main versions of this application form: to fire at the enemy cavalry, or for hunting. These arrows inflict torn and bleeding victim was bleeding quickly. Length - 65 mm.

ATTENTION !!! Tips № 2,3,4 identified only by historical period and origin on the basis of the cultural layer. Identification of the people applying the product, it is very difficult, because while such forms of arrows on the territory of Kievan Rus' was used as a set of Slavs and the nomadic tribes.
So is there a version that tips like number 4 used earlier cultures, living on the territory of modern Ukraine.

Sending worldwide.
